Ah!
啊！

166
00:07:19,720 --> 00:07:20,720
Not on me!
别往我身上扔！

167
00:07:20,720 --> 00:07:21,720
Ah!
啊！

168
00:07:21,720 --> 00:07:27,040
Alright, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

169
00:07:27,040 --> 00:07:31,400
So now we have five more words that we're going to take a look at in Language Takeaway
现在我们要在“语言小课堂”里再看五个词。

170
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:35,600
Part 2.
第二部分。

171
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:36,600
Language Takeaway
语言小课堂。

172
00:07:36,600 --> 00:07:41,360
Okay, so there are lots of fun things to do at the beach.
好的，海滩上有很多好玩的事情可以做。

173
00:07:41,360 --> 00:07:45,040
And today we're not going to be talking about all of them because there are too many things.
今天我们不会全部讲到，因为太多了。

174
00:07:45,040 --> 00:07:47,680
But one fun activity is playing frisbee.
但一个有趣的活动是玩飞盘。

175
00:07:47,680 --> 00:07:49,160
That's right, frisbee.
没错，飞盘。

176
00:07:49,160 --> 00:07:50,160
So this is a thing.
这是一个东西。

177
00:07:50,160 --> 00:07:52,400
It's an object, a frisbee.
它是一个物体，飞盘。

178
00:07:52,400 --> 00:07:54,360
Or you also play frisbee.
或者你也可以说玩飞盘。

179
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:55,360
That's right.
没错。

180
00:07:55,360 --> 00:08:00,200
So a frisbee itself is usually made of plastic and it's like a plate.
飞盘本身通常由塑料制成，像一个盘子。

181
00:08:00,200 --> 00:08:04,920
And it's very light and you throw it to your friends and it sails through the air.
它很轻，你扔给朋友，它会飞过空中。

182
00:08:04,920 --> 00:08:09,200
Right, it kind of flies along the air and then somebody else has to catch it.
对，它有点像在空中飞，然后别人得接住它。

183
00:08:09,200 --> 00:08:10,200
That's right.
没错。

184
00:08:10,200 --> 00:08:12,460
So you can play frisbee or throw the frisbee.
所以你可以说玩飞盘或扔飞盘。

185
00:08:12,460 --> 00:08:16,320
It's very popular with people playing frisbee with their dogs, right?
人们和狗一起玩飞盘很流行，对吧？

186
00:08:16,320 --> 00:08:18,760
You throw the frisbee and the dog chases it.
你扔飞盘，狗去追它。

187
00:08:18,760 --> 00:08:20,480
Dogs love frisbee.
狗喜欢飞盘。

188
00:08:20,480 --> 00:08:25,880
Alright, another great activity that usually we do when we go to the beach is we build
好的，另一个我们通常去海滩时做的好活动是堆沙堡。

189
00:08:25,880 --> 00:08:26,880
sand castles.
沙堡。

190
00:08:26,880 --> 00:08:29,520
Okay, so I'm a master sand castle builder.
好的，我可是堆沙堡的高手。

191
00:08:29,520 --> 00:08:31,600
I'm a really big fan of this activity.
我非常喜欢这个活动。

192
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:32,600
Really?
真的吗？

193
00:08:32,600 --> 00:08:36,720
Basically, you use water and sand to create castles.
基本上，你用水和沙子来建造城堡。

194
00:08:36,720 --> 00:08:41,400
And obviously, you have to use tools like shovels and buckets.
显然，你得用铲子和桶之类的工具。

195
00:08:41,400 --> 00:08:44,480
Otherwise, it might look kind of funny.
否则，它可能会看起来有点滑稽。

196
00:08:44,480 --> 00:08:50,440
And this is actually such a popular activity that there are even competitions at times.
这实际上是一个非常受欢迎的活动，有时甚至会有比赛。

197
00:08:50,440 --> 00:08:57,220
People will not only build castles or houses or structures but maybe a statue of some sort
人们不仅会建造城堡、房子或结构，还可能建造某种雕像。

198
00:08:57,220 --> 00:08:59,320
or an animal or different things.
或者动物或不同的东西。

199
00:08:59,320 --> 00:09:00,320
That's right or people.
没错，或者人像。

200
00:09:00,320 --> 00:09:01,320
People, yeah.
人像，是的。

201
00:09:01,320 --> 00:09:02,880
So sand castle.
所以是沙堡。

202
00:09:02,880 --> 00:09:03,880
Okay.
好的。

203
00:09:03,880 --> 00:09:09,920
And well, whenever we go to the beach, the ocean can be a little bit dangerous.
嗯，每当我们去海滩时，海洋可能有点危险。

204
00:09:09,920 --> 00:09:15,200
And that's why in the dialogue, one of the parents told their kids to stay in the shallow
这就是为什么在对话中，一位家长告诉他们的孩子待在水的浅水区。

205
00:09:15,200 --> 00:09:17,440
area of the water.
浅水区。

206
00:09:17,440 --> 00:09:18,440
That's right.
没错。

207
00:09:18,440 --> 00:09:21,380
So shallow is it describes depth.
所以“浅”是用来描述深度的。

208
00:09:21,380 --> 00:09:22,800
So how deep something is.
也就是某物有多深。

209
00:09:22,800 --> 00:09:26,000
Something is shallow, it's not very deep.
某物是浅的，就不太深。

210
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:27,940
So there's very little water.
所以水很少。

211
00:09:27,940 --> 00:09:32,720
But if there's a lot of water, maybe if you swim and you can't touch your feet on the
但如果水很多，也许你游泳时脚碰不到地。

212
00:09:32,720 --> 00:09:34,980
ground, we call that deep.
我们称之为深。

213
00:09:34,980 --> 00:09:39,560
So shallow is very low water and deep is lots and lots of water.
所以浅是水很浅，深是水很多。

214
00:09:39,560 --> 00:09:40,720
Okay, very good.
好的，非常好。

215
00:09:40,720 --> 00:09:42,740
So you'll usually find this in the ocean.
所以你通常会在海洋里发现这个。

216
00:09:42,740 --> 00:09:47,060
If you go further, further, further in, it'll get deeper and deeper and deeper.
如果你越走越远，水会越来越深。

217
00:09:47,060 --> 00:09:48,480
And more and more dangerous.
而且越来越危险。

218
00:09:48,480 --> 00:09:49,480
Right.
对。

219
00:09:49,480 --> 00:09:56,240
And this is why the mom also told the kid to not pass that sandbar that was ahead.
这也是为什么妈妈还告诉孩子不要越过前面的沙洲。

220
00:09:56,240 --> 00:09:57,440
Okay, sandbar.
好的，沙洲。

221
00:09:57,440 --> 00:10:04,160
This is a piece of sand that basically rises very high in the water.
这是一块沙子，基本上在水里升得很高。

222
00:10:04,160 --> 00:10:07,720
So usually when you're on the beach and you go into the water and it gets deeper and deeper
所以通常当你在海滩上，走进水里，水越来越深。

223
00:10:07,720 --> 00:10:11,340
and then all of a sudden it gets high again and there's more sand.
然后突然又变浅了，有更多沙子。

224
00:10:11,340 --> 00:10:16,320
And so that part that you can stand on, that sand out in the water, that's called a sandbar.
所以你能站在的那部分，水里的沙子，就叫沙洲。

225
00:10:16,320 --> 00:10:17,560
It's almost like a little island.
它几乎像一个小岛。

226
00:10:17,560 --> 00:10:18,920
Yeah, exactly.
是的，没错。

227
00:10:18,920 --> 00:10:23,800
And as you said, usually it gets deeper, deeper, then you have the sandbar so it gets higher.
正如你所说，通常水越来越深，然后有沙洲，所以它变浅了。

228
00:10:23,800 --> 00:10:27,440
But usually if you pass the sandbar, it's going to get really deep all of a sudden.
但通常如果你越过沙洲，它会突然变得非常深。

229
00:10:27,440 --> 00:10:28,440
That's right.
没错。

230
00:10:28,440 --> 00:10:32,240
So that's why the mother doesn't want her child to go past the sandbar.
所以这就是为什么妈妈不想让她的孩子越过沙洲。

231
00:10:32,240 --> 00:10:33,240
Right.
对。

232
00:10:33,240 --> 00:10:37,720
And as well, if you're ever swimming in a swimming pool in the ocean, it's always a
另外，如果你在海洋里游泳，如果你不太会游泳或者有孩子。

233
00:10:37,720 --> 00:10:41,880
good idea if you don't know how to swim well or if you have children to take along little
带上小浮圈总是一个好主意。

234
00:10:41,880 --> 00:10:42,880
floaties.
小浮圈。

235
00:10:42,880 --> 00:10:43,880
Okay, floaties.
好的，小浮圈。

236
00:10:43,880 --> 00:10:46,880
I like this word.
我喜欢这个词。

237
00:10:46,880 --> 00:10:53,640
Floaties are plastic rings that you put around your arms or maybe around your stomach and
小浮圈是塑料环，你套在胳膊上或肚子周围。

238
00:10:53,640 --> 00:10:54,640
they're filled with air.
它们里面充满空气。

239
00:10:54,640 --> 00:10:55,640
Right.
对。

240
00:10:55,640 --> 00:10:57,720
So when you go in the water, they help you float.
所以当你下水时，它们帮你浮起来。

241
00:10:57,720 --> 00:10:58,720
Exactly.
没错。

242
00:10:58,720 --> 00:11:03,200
So this is a very common thing to put on children because they don't know how to swim well.
所以这是很常见给孩子用的东西，因为他们不太会游泳。

243
00:11:03,200 --> 00:11:07,520
So you put them little floaties on their arms or around their stomachs and then they can
你给他们戴上小浮圈在胳膊上或围在肚子上，这样他们就能

244
00:11:07,520 --> 00:11:09,520
just float and they won't drown.
浮在水面上，不会溺水。

245
00:11:09,520 --> 00:11:10,520
That's right.
对。

246
00:11:10,520 --> 00:11:11,520
Floaties.
浮圈。

247
00:11:11,520 --> 00:11:12,520
Very good.
很好。

248
00:11:12,520 --> 00:11:15,720
So a lot of key words there are related to the fun of going to the beach.
所以这里很多关键词都和去海滩的乐趣有关。

249
00:11:15,720 --> 00:11:20,200
Why don't we go back, listen to the dialogue for the very last time.
我们不如回去，再听一遍对话，最后一次。

250
00:11:20,200 --> 00:11:29,320
Oh, George, what a beautiful day it is.
哦，乔治，今天天气真好啊。

251
00:11:29,320 --> 00:11:32,960
The sun is hot and there are just a few clouds scattered here and there.
太阳很热，只有几朵云零星散布。

252
00:11:32,960 --> 00:11:34,800
What a perfect day to be at the beach.
真是去海滩的完美日子。

253
00:11:34,800 --> 00:11:38,720
The kids are going to have so much fun and we'll be able to relax in the sun while they're
孩子们会玩得很开心，我们也能在阳光下放松，而他们

254
00:11:38,720 --> 00:11:40,120
playing.
在玩耍。

255
00:11:40,120 --> 00:11:42,320
It does seem like the perfect day.
看起来确实是完美的一天。

256
00:11:42,320 --> 00:11:46,760
I'm glad we chose to get out of the city and enjoy the nice weather.
我很高兴我们选择离开城市，享受好天气。

257
00:11:46,760 --> 00:11:48,560
This looks like the perfect spot.
这看起来是个完美的地方。

258
00:11:48,560 --> 00:11:53,080
Okay, kids, put on your sunscreen while your mom and I set up camp.
好了，孩子们，涂上防晒霜，我和你妈妈要搭营地了。

259
00:11:53,080 --> 00:11:55,400
Here Mary, help me lay down these beach towels.
玛丽，来帮我铺好这些沙滩巾。

260
00:11:55,400 --> 00:11:56,880
There we go.
好了。

261
00:11:56,880 --> 00:11:58,440
Can you help me with the umbrella?
你能帮我撑伞吗？

262
00:11:58,440 --> 00:11:59,440
Perfect.
完美。

263
00:11:59,440 --> 00:12:01,040
Okay, kids.
好了，孩子们。

264
00:12:01,040 --> 00:12:03,960
Here's a beach ball and a frisbee, a pail and a shovel.
这里有沙滩球、飞盘、桶和铲子。

265
00:12:03,960 --> 00:12:08,640
I want to see an impressive sand castle by the time we leave.
我想在我们离开前看到一个令人印象深刻的沙堡。

266
00:12:08,640 --> 00:12:09,880
Don't stray too far.
别走太远。

267
00:12:09,880 --> 00:12:12,800
Wait, leave your sandals here or put on your wet shoes.
等等，把凉鞋留在这里，或者穿上湿鞋。

268
00:12:12,800 --> 00:12:14,280
And stay in the shallow area.
待在浅水区。

269
00:12:14,280 --> 00:12:17,200
I don't want to see you go any further than that sandbar.
我不想看到你们游过那个沙洲。

270
00:12:17,200 --> 00:12:20,000
It's too deep out there and we didn't bring your floaties.
那边太深了，我们没带你们的浮圈。

271
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:21,280
You're back already?
你们这么快就回来了？

272
00:12:21,280 --> 00:12:23,280
The water was too cold, huh?
水太冷了，是吧？

273
00:12:23,280 --> 00:12:24,560
I'll tell you a secret.
我告诉你们一个秘密。

274
00:12:24,560 --> 00:12:27,760
Do you see that small pool of water over there?
你看到那边那个小水坑了吗？

275
00:12:27,760 --> 00:12:28,760
It'll be warmer in there.
那里会更暖和。

276
00:12:28,760 --> 00:12:32,120
Go see if you can find some seashells or catch some minnows.
去看看能不能找到一些贝壳或捉些小鱼。

277
00:12:32,120 --> 00:12:33,120
Ah!
啊！

278
00:12:33,120 --> 00:12:34,120
What is that?
那是什么？

279
00:12:34,120 --> 00:12:35,120
A jellyfish?
水母吗？

280
00:12:35,120 --> 00:12:37,400
Jeremy, put that down right now.
杰里米，马上放下那个。

281
00:12:37,400 --> 00:12:39,040
It could sting you.
它会蜇你的。

282
00:12:39,040 --> 00:12:40,040
Ah!
啊！

283
00:12:40,040 --> 00:12:43,040
Not on me!
别扔到我身上！

284
00:12:43,040 --> 00:12:44,040
Ah!
啊！

285
00:12:44,040 --> 00:12:50,120
All right, so beach activities.
好了，所以海滩活动。

286
00:12:50,120 --> 00:12:52,480
You say you're a master sand castle builder.
你说你是沙堡建造大师。

287
00:12:52,480 --> 00:12:53,760
I love building sand castles.
我喜欢建沙堡。

288
00:12:53,760 --> 00:12:55,840
I won't say that I'm very good at it.
我不会说我非常擅长。

289
00:12:55,840 --> 00:12:57,480
Maybe not a professional.
可能不是专业的。

290
00:12:57,480 --> 00:13:00,080
But I do a pretty good sand castle.
但我建的沙堡还不错。

291
00:13:00,080 --> 00:13:02,480
Do you like getting buried in the sand?
你喜欢被埋在沙子里吗？

292
00:13:02,480 --> 00:13:03,480
I love it.
我喜欢。

293
00:13:03,480 --> 00:13:04,480
Really?
真的吗？

294
00:13:04,480 --> 00:13:05,480
Although it also scares me.
虽然也让我有点害怕。

295
00:13:05,480 --> 00:13:08,400
Have you ever had someone maybe cover you with sand and then you can't move?
你有没有过别人把你埋在沙子里，然后你动不了？

296
00:13:08,400 --> 00:13:09,400
Yeah.
有。

297
00:13:09,400 --> 00:13:11,680
Yeah, so it's a little bit scary.
是啊，所以有点吓人。

298
00:13:11,680 --> 00:13:15,480
Obviously I'm not very comfortable with having my head covered.
显然我不太舒服把头埋起来。

299
00:13:15,480 --> 00:13:16,840
But some people even do that.
但有些人甚至那样做。

300
00:13:16,840 --> 00:13:19,760
They cover their entire body, head to toe.
他们埋全身，从头到脚。

301
00:13:19,760 --> 00:13:20,760
How do they breathe?
他们怎么呼吸？

302
00:13:20,760 --> 00:13:23,400
And they have a straw out of their mouth to breathe.
他们嘴里插根吸管来呼吸。

303
00:13:23,400 --> 00:13:24,400
Wow.
哇。

304
00:13:24,400 --> 00:13:29,880
I actually love going to the beach and it's relaxing, it's really fun.
我其实很喜欢去海滩，很放松，也很有趣。

305
00:13:29,880 --> 00:13:33,240
But I don't really enjoy it going when there are a lot of people.
但我不太喜欢人很多的时候去。

306
00:13:33,240 --> 00:13:35,040
Because I like to relax on the beach.
因为我喜欢在海滩上放松。

307
00:13:35,040 --> 00:13:39,560
But when there are too many people, they're running around, there are kids running around
但人太多时，他们跑来跑去，孩子们到处跑，

308
00:13:39,560 --> 00:13:41,040
and it's not very relaxing.
就不太放松了。

309
00:13:41,040 --> 00:13:42,800
Yeah, I hear you.
是啊，我懂你的意思。

310
00:13:42,800 --> 00:13:45,600
But swimming in the ocean is also very dangerous, right?
但在海里游泳也很危险，对吧？

311
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:46,800
It can be.
有可能。

312
00:13:46,800 --> 00:13:52,160
So we recommend you go places where there are lifeguards on duty or that you go with
所以我们建议你去有救生员值班的地方，或者和

313
00:13:52,160 --> 00:13:53,160
an expert swimmer.
游泳高手一起去。

314
00:13:53,160 --> 00:13:54,160
Lifeguards.
救生员。

315
00:13:54,160 --> 00:13:55,160
Yeah.
是的。

316
00:13:55,160 --> 00:13:56,440
That's all we've got though for today.
不过今天我们就讲到这里。

317
00:13:56,440 --> 00:13:59,840
We hope you've enjoyed this lesson and we hope you're excited about the upcoming summer
我们希望你喜欢这节课，也希望你对即将到来的夏季

318
00:13:59,840 --> 00:14:00,840
months.
月份感到兴奋。

319
00:14:00,840 --> 00:14:03,960
If you have any questions or comments, please do visit our website EnglishPod.com.
如果你有任何问题或评论，请访问我们的网站 EnglishPod.com。

320
00:14:03,960 --> 00:14:04,960
All right.
好的。

321
00:14:04,960 --> 00:14:05,960
We'll see you guys there.
我们到时候见。

322
00:14:05,960 --> 00:14:06,960
Bye.
拜拜。

323
00:14:06,960 --> 00:14:25,840
All right.
好的。

324
00:14:25,840 --> 00:14:30,420
Man.
天哪。

325
00:14:30,420 --> 00:14:34,880
All right.
好的。
